documentation.text:
@dev Contract Variables:
 assetRouterApproved - Approved UnoAssetRouter contracts.
 accessManager - Role manager contract.
 autoStrategyBeacon - AutoStrategy contract implementation.
 autoStrategies - List of deployed AutoStrategy contracts.
@dev Deploys new AutoStrategy contract and calls initialize() on it. Emits {AutoStrategyDeployed} event.

Paused(address).details: Emitted when the pause is triggered by `account`.

Unpaused(address).details: Emitted when the pause is lifted by `account`.

approveAssetRouter(address).details: Approves an address for use as an AssetRouter. Emits {AssetRouterApproved} event.

params._assetRouter: - Asset router address to approve. Note: This function can only be called by ADMIN_ROLE.

createStrategy((address,address)[]).details: Checks if provided assetRouters are approved for use, then deploys new AutoStrategy contract.

params.poolInfos: - An array of (assetRouter - pool) pairs. AssetRouter needs to be approved for PoolInfo to be valid. poolInfos.length must be >= 2.

returns._0: autoStrategy - Deployed Auto Strategy contract address.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

revokeAssetRouter(address).details: Revokes Asset Router approval from an address. Emits {AssetRouterRevoked} event.

params._assetRouter: - Address to revoke approval from. Note: This function can only be called by ADMIN_ROLE.

upgradeStrategies(address).details: Upgrade all AutoStrategy contracts to a new implementation using Beacon Proxy.

params.newImplementation: - New AutoStrategy implementation. Note: This function can only be called by ADMIN_ROLE.

assetRouterApproved.details: Contract Variables: assetRouterApproved - Approved UnoAssetRouter contracts. accessManager - Role manager contract. autoStrategyBeacon - AutoStrategy contract implementation. autoStrategies - List of deployed AutoStrategy contracts.
